1 warrant make payment for the correct amount. The treasurer
2 may make payment by issuing a check or warrant or by using
3 an electronic payment method or fund transfer system. Any
4 check or warrant shall be signed by the mayor and
5 countersigned by the treasurer or any other person the
6 governing body designates to countersign checks or warrants
7 in the treasurer's absence. If there is not sufficient
8 money in the treasury to pay the warrant, the treasurer
9 shall endorse on the warrant the date and a statement that
10 it has been presented for payment but has not been paid for
11 want of funds. Thereafter, the warrant shall draw interest
12 at the rate of ten percent (10%) per year.
13
14 15-4-302. Finances; warrants; use for disbursements;
15 exception; limitations; contents; procedure.
16
17 (a) Except as otherwise provided by law, all
18 disbursements shall be made by check or warrant signed by
19 the manager and countersigned by the mayor or by using an
20 electronic payment method or fund transfer system. No check
21 or warrant may be drawn in payment of a claim, and no
22 electronic payment or fund transfer may be made, of more
23 than fifty dollars ($50.00) until the claim is certified by
