5
6 18-3-511. Presentation, auditing and payment of
7 claims; issuance of tax-anticipation warrants; limitation
8 and form of warrants; effect of acceptance.
9
10 (a) All claims and demands against a county shall be
11 presented for audit and allowance to the board of county
12 commissioners before any action in court is maintainable.
13 All claims when allowed shall be paid in accordance with
14 this subsection. Claims may be paid by using an electronic
15 payment method or fund transfer system or by a county
16 warrant or order drawn by the board on the county treasurer
17 upon the proper funds in the treasury for the amount of the
18 claims. The Any warrant or order shall be signed by the
19 permanent or temporary chairman of the board, attested by
20 the county clerk under the seal of the county, and
21 countersigned and registered by the county treasurer. The
22 warrant or order shall specify the amount of the claim or
23 service and be numbered and dated in the order in which it
