2 warrants and orders are payable on demand and shall be
3 drawn and issued upon the county treasurer only when there
4 are sufficient monies in the appropriate fund in the
5 treasury to pay such warrants and orders make the required
6 payments.
7
8 18-3-810. Restrictions upon countersigning warrants.
9
10 No county treasurer shall countersign any blank county
11 order or warrant or other order or warrant, or make any
12 electronic payment or fund transfer, until he the treasurer
13 is satisfied that the electronic payment, order or warrant
14 was ordered drawn by the board of county commissioners.
15
16 18-3-811. Register of county orders and payments.
17
18 Each county treasurer shall keep in his office a book
19 called the register of county orders wherein shall be
20 entered on the date of the presentation thereof and without
21 interval or blank line between any entry and the one
22 preceding it every county order, warrant, electronic
23 payment or other certificate or evidence of county
